  "name": "Cast Iron Laser Cleaning Dataset",
  "description": "When cleaning cast iron, we've found its inherent porosity serves as a natural benefit, pulling in laser energy to break loose tough rust and scale on heavy industrial components, but you need to begin with careful power levels from the start to avoid any chance of surface cracking due to the material's relative brittleness, in the end bringing back its strength for automotive and machinery uses while keeping structural integrity intact",
